&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Sand&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.sandtech.com/&quot;&gt;Sand Technologies&lt;/a&gt; is a global Physical AI company using data and AI to make critical industries work better. We partner with governments, cities and enterprises to improve how essential systems operate across healthcare, water, energy, telecommunications and infrastructure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our work delivers proven real-world impact. We have built AI systems that help manage London’s water supply, supported telecom network planning across hundreds of cities, and developed digital healthcare platforms serving tens of millions of people across Africa. From intelligent command centers to AI-powered infrastructure platforms, we help organizations sense, analyze and act in complex environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our people are ambitious, curious and relentlessly practical. Our teams work alongside clients in the field, solving hard problems and deploying solutions that last. With colleagues across Africa, Europe, the UK and the US, we operate across the full stack - from research and engineering to deployment and capability building.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our mission is simple: to harness AI to solve humanity’s most pressing challenges.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role owns the requirements and analytical work across the full delivery lifecycle alongside the technical lead, from requirements discovery and sprint planning through to UAT, documentation governance, and value tracking.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Business Analyst operates semi-autonomously alongside the product owner to support the “what” and the “why” of solution’s development for our client. They own client relationships, maintain and improve analytical standards for the squad, manage the full artefact estate, and provide mentorship to our junior Business Analyst team members where possible. They are expected to bring a point of view and resolve scope, stakeholder, and quality challenges without defaulting to escalation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements &amp;amp; Backlog Ownership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the BA workstream by driving discovery efforts, framing problems, and managing the product backlog across near, mid, and far horizons.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write, refine, and validate user stories and clear acceptance criteria while championing a culture of Continuous Discovery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a strategic thought partner to the Product Owner, stepping in as the de facto PO to prioritize use cases and guide solution direction when necessary.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stakeholder Facilitation &amp;amp; Engagement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Independently design and facilitate requirements workshops, design conferences, and process walkthroughs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage complex, multi-level stakeholder relationships across client and delivery organizations (including technical, financial, and executive sponsors).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively communicate progress, scope changes, and risks to build client confidence through reliable, outcome-focused engagement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Analysis &amp;amp; Documentation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce and maintain comprehensive documentation, including BRDs, FSDs, user stories, and BPMN-aligned As-Is/To-Be process models.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with engineering teams to define data requirements, source systems, and transformation logic.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Curate the squad’s knowledge base, playbooks, and reusable artifacts to ensure consistent delivery standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
