&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.sandtech.com/&quot;&gt;Sand Technologies&lt;/a&gt; is a fast-growing enterprise AI company that solves real-world problems for large blue-chip companies and governments worldwide.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’re pioneers of meaningful AI&lt;/strong&gt;: our solutions go far beyond chatbots. We are using data and AI to solve the world’s biggest issues in telecommunications, sustainable water management, energy, healthcare, climate change, smart cities, and other areas that have a real impact on the world. For example, our AI systems help to manage the water supply for the entire city of London. We created the AI algorithms that enabled the 7th largest telecommunications company in the world to plan its network in 300 cities in record time. And we built a digital healthcare system that enables 30m people in a country to get world-class healthcare despite a shortage of doctors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’ve grown our revenues by over 500% in the last 12 months while winning prestigious scientific and industry awards for our cutting-edge technology. Our success is supported by about 300 engineers and scientists working across Africa, Europe, the UK, and the US.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sand is expanding across Africa and beyond, partnering with governments and public sector officials to deliver transformative AI and data solutions. Our flagship healthcare initiative - the &lt;strong&gt;Health Operating System (HOS)&lt;/strong&gt; - is already live. In Rwanda, hundreds of clinics have already been digitized, transforming rural facilities into next-generation health centers that are redefining care in Africa. Sand’s groundbreaking HOS data products, and clinical systems to drive better outcomes - from maternal health to chronic disease management - are already reaching more than 1 million patients. Designed for digital empowerment, the HOS equips thousands of frontline health workers with the tools and support they need to magnify their impact and strengthen community health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now, we are scaling rapidly. By the end of 2025, our HOS will be operational in &lt;strong&gt;10 countries&lt;/strong&gt;, and by 2026, we plan to expand even further across the continent. This is not an idea — it’s already happening, and the momentum is accelerating. But healthcare is only one example; Sand is growing in various industries, namely water, energy, and telecommunications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an in-country &lt;strong&gt;Forward Deployed Engineer,&lt;/strong&gt; you will be responsible for the end-to-end deployment, integration, and performance of Sand’s technology systems across healthcare, water, energy, or telecommunications. This includes ensuring seamless data capture, exchange, and governance between government systems and Sand’s platforms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is both strategic and hands-on - requiring a strong technical foundation, excellent problem-solving skills, and the ability to translate system performance into real-world healthcare impact. Beyond deployment, you will play a key role in engaging with ministries and IT teams to ensure access to systems, alignment on data-sharing agreements, and adherence to national data standards. Your understanding of data management processes - from data capture workflows to interoperability and quality assurance - will be crucial to enabling reliable reporting, analytics, and decision-making at national scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Specific Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;System Deployment:&lt;/strong&gt; Hands-on technical implementation and rollout of Sand’s solutions in-country.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Integration Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Ensure interoperability with existing systems and technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;stro

