&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Forward Deployed Engineers (FDEs) are Sand’s frontline inside our most strategic customers; embedding directly within client teams to unlock data, building lightweight production solutions, and compressing time-to-value from months to weeks. This is not staff augmentation. This is a value-engineering role: hands-on, deeply technical, fast, and focused on proving ROI in real operational environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an FDE, you will sit inside one of our US industries—Energy, Utilities, or Public Sector—and be deployed full-time on-site with a client. You will work shoulder-to-shoulder with operators, engineers, analysts, and executives to identify opportunities, access and shape data, prove value through rapid prototyping, and deploy solutions that drive measurable financial and operational outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your work directly shapes commercial expansion, platform evolution, and the credibility of Sand in the most complex asset-heavy environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is ideal for a technically strong engineer or scientist who thrives in ambiguity, loves solving real-world problems in the field, and has the communication and resilience needed to earn trust inside demanding customer environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Specific Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1. Value Engineering &amp;amp; Rapid Solution Delivery&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Embed directly inside the client to unlock data, map value streams, and build lightweight production-grade solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute rapid analysis, prototyping, and iterative validation using wrangling tools, secure sandboxes, and proven patterns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver measurable outcomes within weeks—fast deployments, clear ROI proof points, and visible operational value.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2. Technical Execution &amp;amp; On-site Delivery&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
